author: Nicolas Perpitch
title: WA records 14 new COVID-19 cases, but almost all traced to cruise ships and overseas travel
description: Western Australia records 14 new cases of COVID-19, with all but one from cruise ships and overseas travel, providing further evidence community spread of the virus is being limited, according to WA's Health Minister.
content:
Posted 
April 04, 2020 16:20:28
Western Australia has recorded 14 new cases of COVID-19, including five from the Artania cruise ship, which Health Minister Roger Cook says is further evidence community spread of the virus is being limited.
